TROUBLESHOOTING


ON THE SLAVE SERVER WHERE TOMCAT IS INSTALLED 


# Check if Tomcat is listening locally

netstat -tunlp | grep 8080

# Check if the Manager app is responding (Should return 401 Unauthorized)

curl -I http://localhost:8080/manager/html




2.

The AWS Firewall Check
If curl localhost:8080 works but you can't see the app in your browser:
	• Action: Go to EC2 Security Groups and add Inbound Rule for Port 8080 from 0.0.0.0/0.




3.


The Restart Protocol
If you change context.xml or tomcat-users.xml, Tomcat must be restarted manually if it isn't a systemd service:
Bash

/opt/tomcat/bin/shutdown.sh
/opt/tomcat/bin/startup.sh
